@PaulW 

> If you truncate & slugify the names, you can still hit this condition where multiple pods can be returned.

Sorry if I misunderstand but I am not sure I see how this would happen. Just to be clear, what I am proposing is that if the current dag_id label is `> 63` characters long, you slugify by truncating to `n` characters and add a `m` characters-long hash of the extra characters at the end of the slug to guarantee uniqueness, where `n + m + 1 <= 63` (with +1 to account for some separator between the truncated name part and the hash part of the slug). So you would end up with slugs that look like `dagidtaskid-hash` instead of just `hash`.

@ashb I've prepared a PR that deletes all inline styles
https://github.com/apache/airflow/pull/4823
After its merge, I will return to this PR

@RosterIn Agree. `try_get` is a better name 👍 

EDIT:
Changed function name from `optional` to `try_get` and also updated the doc change in this PR, as well as the PR body.

@feng-tao actually no bug fixes in 2.6 or 2.6.1.

Pinning the upper bound earlier in https://github.com/apache/airflow/pull/4800 was only due to wrong wheel build in 2.6, not breaking change, so I thought it may be good to unpin it given 2.6.1 works well.

It's ok to me to keep the upper bound as well. Please feel free to close this PR in that case.
